article.description: Jessica Mooney scored 16 points, fellow reserve Chanel Chisolm added 13 and No. 16 Vanderbilt cruised to a 78-41 victory over winless Radford on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Reserves team up to help Vanderbilt run over Radford
article.linkText: Vandy scores easy victory over winless Radford
article.story:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Jessica Mooney scored 16 points, fellow reserve Chanel Chisolm added 13 and No. 16 Vanderbilt cruised to a 78-41 victory over winless Radford on Tuesday night.

Mooney shot 6-of-10 from the field in 20 minutes off the bench, and Chisolm was 5-for-6 in 13 minutes. Mooney also had four assists and two steals.

Hannah Tuomi was the only Commodores starter in double figures. She had 10 points and six rebounds.

Vanderbilt (7-1) held Radford scoreless for the first 3:33 and led 23-6 following Mooney's layup with 8:45 left in the first half.

Radford (0-6) committed 29 turnovers and made only 13 baskets. Vandy Pullen led the Highlanders with 14 points.
